data.text:
Scattering regularity for small data solutions to the nonlinear Schrödinger equation. With Andrew Hassell and Sean Gomes. On arxiv.

Price's law on Minkowski space in the presence of an inverse square potential. With Dean Baskin and Jeremy Marzuola. On arxiv.

Propagation of singularities and Fredholm analysis of the time-dependent Schrödinger equation. With Andrew Hassell and Sean Gomes. To appear in American Journal of Mathematics. On arxiv.

Asymptotics of the radiation field for the massless Dirac-Coulomb system. With Dean Baskin and Robert Booth. On arxiv. To appear in Journal of Functional Analysis.

Regularity of the scattering matrix for nonlinear Helmholtz Eigenfunctions. With Jacob Shapiro and Andrew Hassell. On arxiv. To appear in Journal of Spectral Theory.

Riemann moduli spaces are quantum ergodic WithDean Baskin,Xiaolong Han. arXiv link. Journal of Differential Geometry. Volume 123 (2023), no. 3, 391-410

The index formula for families of Dirac-type operators on pseudomanifolds. WithPierre Albin. Onarxiv. To appear in Journal of Differential Geom.

Existence and asymptotics of nonlinear Helmholtz eigenfunctions WithAndrew Hassell, Jacob Shapiro, Junyong Zhang. SIAM J. Math. Anal. 52 (2020), no. 6, 6180-6221.

Spectral and Hodge theory of `Witt' incomplete cusp edge spaces. WithJan Swoboda. arXiv link. To appear in Commentarii Mathematici Helvetici. 94 (2019), no. 4, 701-765

Equidistribution of phase shifts in obstacle scattering. With Maxime Ingremeau. arXiv link. Comm. Partial Differential Equations. Volume 44, Issue 1, (2019), 1–19

The distribution of phase shifts for semiclassical potentials with polynomial decay. WithAndrew Hassell. IMRN. Vol 2020, no. 19.

The index of Dirac operators on incomplete edge spaces. WithPierre Albin. SIGMA 12 (2016), 089, 45 pages

The Feynman propagator on perturbations of Minkowski space. With Nick Haber, andAndras Vasy. Communications in Mathematical Physics, Volume 342, Issue 1, 2016, Pages 333–384.

Harmonic maps into conic surfaces with cone angles less than 2π. Communications in Analysis and Geometry, Volume 23, Issue 4, 2015, Pages 717–796
